    <item>
      <title>Transmetropolitan, Vol. 4: The New Scum</title>
      <link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2021/09/04/transmetropolitan-vol.-4-the-new-scum/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 04 Sep 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2021/09/04/transmetropolitan-vol.-4-the-new-scum/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;cover-image&#34;&gt;
                &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;22421&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22421.transmetropolitan-vol-4-the-new-scum&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/transmetropolitan-vol-4-the-new-scum.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
            &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mostly, it&amp;rsquo;s a story about interviewing the candidates for election and answering that age old &amp;lsquo;which is the lesser evil&amp;rsquo; sort of question. Or I suppose in this question, can Spider find enough to convince him not to go outright nuclear on both of them and screw the world over even worse?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s fascinating seeing both women in the cast now. Bit weird.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
